node.text:
Black entrepreneurs have less access to funding, mentorship, and growth opportunities, and they are significantly underrepresented in retail.

That’s why Amazon is launching the Black Business Accelerator and committing $150 million to this effort. It will help build sustainable equity and growth for Black-owned businesses that sell on Amazon.

Learn more at amazon.com/bba. [link in bio]
